<taxonomicName id="C8DD65ECBD599287DF9C951F7D3DDA6F" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Porodaedalea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Porodaedalea" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Porodaedalea</taxonomicName>
sp. (fleshy polypore) on dead standing beech tree (1 ♂, RWC). Queens Co., Cranberry Lake P.N.A, 
<geoCoordinate id="BEA86586CD8C5A9BFBB6A1C4ED8ADC91" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="5" value="46.1125">46.1125°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="A4DEB7C967B472B00696F2EB42FD6BC3" direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="5" value="-65.6075">65.6075°W</geoCoordinate>
, 11-18.VI.2009, R. Webster &amp; M.-A. 
<normalizedToken id="26FBE83BB74E9AD4A05D9ED572D2E055" originalValue="Giguère">Giguere</normalizedToken>
, old red oak forest, Lindgren funnel trap (1, AFC).
</paragraph>
